title: Untold Tales of Spider-Man
description:
Untold Tales of Spider-Man is the name of an American comic book series starring Spider-Man published by Marvel Comics for 26 issues (#1-25, and a #Minus 1 between #s 22 and 23) from September, 1995 to October, 1997. 

The series was primarily written by Kurt Busiek and pencilled by Pat Olliffe, though Roger Stern, Tom DeFalco and Ron Frenz also contributed. Tom Brevoort was the editor of the title throughout its run. The critical and fan approval of the comic boosted Brevoort and Busiek&#039;s career and by the time the series had finished both had achieved key positions on the bestselling Heroes Return titles Avengers and Iron Man.
